---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/it-support/Header.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="Enterprise IT Asset Audit Automation | Noor Azami"
    description="Automated IT asset compliance tracking using a smart rate-limited Python script to dispatch targeted notifications without system bottlenecks."
>
    <Header />
    <main class="pt-16">
        <!-- Back Button -->
        <div class="px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-4">
            <a
                href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL}
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-text-secondary hover:text-white transition-colors group cursor-pointer"
            >
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"></path>
                </svg>
                Back to Dashboard
            </a>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Project Hero Section -->
        <section class="py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
                <div class="text-center mb-12 fade-in-scroll">
                    <div class="flex justify-center mb-6">
                        <span class="px-6 py-3 bg-green-500/20 text-green-400 border border-green-500/30 rounded-full font-semibold">IT Asset Automation</span>
                    </div>
                    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
                        Enterprise IT Asset Audit Automation
                    </h1>
                    <p class="text-xl text-text-secondary max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                        A robust Python-based automation suite designed to streamline IT hardware auditing, utilizing logic blocks for targeted employee notifications and active data self-cleaning.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Project Overview -->
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-16">
                    <div class="card fade-in-scroll">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Project Type</h3>
                        <p class="text-text-secondary">
                            Backend Scripting / Process Automation / Data Ops
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card fade-in-scroll">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Tech Stack</h3>
                        <p class="text-text-secondary">
                            Python, Pandas, OpenPyXL, win32com (Outlook COM Automation)
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card fade-in-scroll">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Core Functions</h3>
                        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-500/20 text-blue-400 border border-blue-500/30 rounded text-sm">Rate Limiting</span>
                            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-green-500/20 text-green-400 border border-green-500/30 rounded text-sm">Data Parsing</span>
                            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-purple-500/20 text-purple-400 border border-purple-500/30 rounded text-sm">Auto-Clean CSV</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- GitHub CTA for Diagram -->
                <div class="bg-gray-800/50 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-8 mb-16 text-center shadow-xl fade-in-scroll">
                    <span class="text-5xl block mb-6">🗺️</span>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Architecture & Code Repository</h3>
                    <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">
                        The complete operational flowchart detailing the script's execution path—from Excel extraction up to targeted email blasting and data sanitization—is fully documented in the GitHub repository.
                    </p>
                    <a href="https://github.com/AmiQT/it-asset-automation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-8 py-4 bg-white text-gray-900 rounded-lg font-bold hover:bg-gray-200 transition-colors shadow-lg">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 0c-6.626 0-12 5.373-12 12 0 5.302 3.438 9.8 8.207 11.387.599.111.793-.261.793-.577v-2.234c-3.338.726-4.033-1.416-4.033-1.416-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23.957-.266 1.983-.399 3.003-.404 1.02.005 2.047.138 3.006.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222v3.293c0 .319.192.694.801.576 4.765-1.589 8.199-6.086 8.199-11.386 0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12z"/></svg>
                        View Diagram & Code
                    </a>
                </div>

                <!-- Documentation Content -->
                <div class="mb-16 fade-in-scroll">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">System Logic & Capabilities</h2>

                    <!-- Section 1 -->
                    <div class="space-y-6 mb-12">
                        <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-6">
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">1. Automated Data Ingestion</h3>
                            <div class="bg-gray-800/30 border border-gray-700 rounded p-4 mb-4">
                                <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                                    The script automatically ingests the raw `.xlsx` inventory file downloaded from the enterprise portal. Using the powerful <strong>Pandas</strong> library, it flawlessly converts the complex spreadsheet into a simplified, working `.csv` file for rapid and safe data extraction without altering the original record.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Section 2 -->
                    <div class="space-y-6 mb-12">
                        <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6">
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">2. Smart Rate Limiting & Broadcasting</h3>
                            <div class="bg-gray-800/30 border border-gray-700 rounded p-4 mb-4">
                                <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                                    To prevent system bottlenecks and server throttling from dispatch functions, the algorithm incorporates a <strong>throttle control</strong> mechanism. It iterates through the target list of untagged employees in controlled batches, implementing sleep intervals to ensure stable, reliable delivery of messages or Emails.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Section 3 -->
                    <div class="space-y-6 mb-12">
                        <div class="border-l-4 border-yellow-500 pl-6">
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">3. Data Sanitization (Self-Cleaning)</h3>
                            <div class="bg-gray-800/30 border border-gray-700 rounded p-4 mb-4">
                                <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                                    Once a notification blast is successful, the script executes a self-cleaning routine. It <strong>auto-removes</strong> the processed user from the working `.csv` file. This guarantees that if the script halts or runs again against the file, the dataset only retains pending/untargeted records—completely eliminating the risk of sending duplicate notifications.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Section 4 -->
                    <div class="space-y-6 mb-12">
                        <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-6">
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">4. Continuous Auditing & Logging</h3>
                            <div class="bg-gray-800/30 border border-gray-700 rounded p-4 mb-4">
                                <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                                    For strict corporate accountability, every successful dispatch and handled error is written synchronously into a local `Audit_Log.txt`. This creates a reliable trail of executed actions for Tech Leads and IT Managers to review post-execution.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- AI Empowerment Section -->
                    <div class="bg-blue-900/20 border border-blue-700 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
                            🤖 AI-Empowered Development
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
                            This project was developed using a modern <strong>AI-assisted workflow</strong>. By leveraging advanced LLMs (Gemini & GitHub Copilot), the development process was accelerated and optimized:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-secondary">
                            <li>• <strong>Logic Optimization</strong>: Used AI to refactor and optimize the core rate-limiting algorithm for maximum SMTP stability.</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Rapid Prototyping</strong>: Accelerated the integration of Pandas batch processing through AI-driven code generation.</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Error Resilience</strong>: Implemented robust exception handling blocks identified through AI-assisted edge-case analysis.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Project Impact -->
                    <div class="bg-green-900/20 border border-green-700 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
                            🚀 Business Impact
                        </h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-secondary">
                            <li>• Reduced manual asset tracking time by up to <strong>90%</strong>.</li>
                            <li>• Streamlined compliance and security enforcement for hardware verification.</li>
                            <li>• Eliminated human-error in tracking large volumes of 200+ employees.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>
